### JavaWebPrj — REST API tests (IntelliJ: open this file → green arrow next to each request)
### App must be running on http://localhost:8080

### STEP 1 — Get JWT token (no auth needed)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "customer",
  "password": "customer123"
}

### Copy the "token" value from the response, then paste it below as YOUR_TOKEN
### Or use IntelliJ: after step 1, set token from response (manual)

### STEP 2 — List all products (JWT required)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### STEP 3 — Products in category 1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products?categoryId=1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### STEP 4 — One product by id
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### STEP 5 — Without token (should fail 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products
